Row.Text: Greetings. I am the Chief Justice, or "Iudex" of Fontaine, but you may simply address me by using my surname, "Neuvillette." Not because I wish to keep my distance from you... No, I am merely conscious that being overly familiar may bring the impartiality of the judiciary into question in some people's eyes.
I'm sure I'll be back when the waves come back...
What will you offer?
Greeting. What business do you have today?
Welcome.
I am doing official business, and have no time to spare on the likes of you.
Your people are an affluent one, I see.
Will you not sign a research agreement with me?
I usually keep my distance with others to be impartial. But a friendship with you should not prove problematic. I will lend you my strength.
This resource is what we need. Will you not agree to a trade?
I'd like our nations to open our borders and exchange goods and culture. What say you?
It was a fine deal. Shall we continue this?
Thank you for freeing our prisoned people.
If you admit your espionage without resistance, I will forgive that transgression just this once.
You are either bold or brazen to send spies even though you know they will be caught.
Your spy is full of holes to say the least.
Law and order can only exist on the back of might. Empty words like freedom and equality only dirsupts it.
Law and order can only exist on the foundation of freedom and equality. Law and order without those things are mere barbarity.
Law and order can only exist through revoultion. Law and order not found through revolution is merely a tool of the bourgeoisie.
I have no intent on matching your offer.
Our people are going to listen to the performance at the Epichles Opera House and apply for the Marechaussee Phantom. I'm worried that your Fontaine will eat into the world.
I did not expect Fontaine to prosper like this.

Why are you just standing there with your mouth gaping? Ah, you must be stunned and at a loss for words... Understandable, it is I after all... Fontaine's most beloved star, Furina. I'm on a very tight schedule, so you're lucky to even get an appointment with me.
Is this... a form of liberation?
Hi?
What's up?
That resource is what we need, so why don't you trade?
That resource is what we need, so why don't you trade?
There will be a lot of benefits for each other if we open our borders.
Do you have any suggestions?
Hi. Would you like to chat with me if you don't mind?
Originally, you can't meet me easily, but you're an exception.
Did you come to see my performance?
I don't have time to see you because I'm busy.
I don't want to see you?
You look pretty rich. If you don't mind, why don't you sponsor our stage later?
I'm sorry, but I can't afford to meet the proposal.
Did you just spy on me? You have a lot of guts.
I don't want to, but if you admit to being a spy, I'll overlook you for once.
Your spy is really full of loopholes.
What a waste of a spy's life, it's pathetic.
Wouldn't it be better to make a research agreement with each other?
Those who lead the stage need strong power and leadership.
The importance of freedom and equality on the stage is, to say the least, painful.
A stage without a revolution is nothing but a deep-rooted evil. It's about flipping everything and creating a new stage.
Wouldn't it be better to form an alliance with each other?
Our alliance is strong, right? Then it goes without saying.
Our alliance is strong, right? Then it goes without saying.
Wouldn't it be better to form an alliance with each other?
I liked this deal. Do you want to trade again?
Okay.
Let's do it.
Thank you for your consideration.
I thank you on behalf of Fontaine.
Do you have any other suggestions?
The proposal is not very attractive.
I'm not interested in the proposal at all.
That's a ridiculous suggestion?
Thank you for saving Fontaine's citizens.
Our people are fascinated by your stage and want to become Opera Actors. I am worried that your Fontaine will eat into the world.
As expected, my performance has the power to attract everyone. It feels good to see so many people come to see my performance?
